#show: template

#taxon[Idea]
// #title[Title]

We can show, that being _abelian_ is independed of the other group axioms by constucting a group that is _abelian_ and a group that is _not abelian_.
Assuming our theory is consistent, this ought to be possible if and only if being _abelian_ is independend of the other axioms.
